author: Kazuma Kiryu
text: 3 years ago, I laid in bed, in the middle of a major depressive episode, on the verge of committing suicide. I felt hopeless, like my existence in this world was nothing but futile, like I was fated for pain. I just wanted an end to it all. I wanted to die. But being an avid fan of music, I just wanted to listen to my favorite music one last time. This included soundtracks to my favorite games. As I opened my playlist and listened through, I laid, crying, bawling my eyes out, and planning what I would write for my friends and family. That's when I reached a certain piece of music. That piece was Forest Interlude. I curled up in a ball and cried. I bawled. Memories of DKC2 flashed through my mind... the first time I played it... a gift from my grandmother. I replayed it, and kept doing so for an hour, bawling all the while. I didn't want to make my grandmother upset. I wanted to enjoy the beauty of this world, despite my pain. Now, here I am. I've met the love of my life, have wonderful and kind friends who I love very much and love me very much, I'm on the cusp of beginning college, and most importantly, I'm alive. The point is that life does get better. I never believed it myself but it does. And someday you'll have something or someone to thank for hanging in there. And your struggles, your pain, will just be a memory. You have people who love you. Who care for you. Even if it doesn't seem like it. We love you, this comment section. Somewhere, there will always be someone to talk to and love you. I promise. I'd be lying if I said it isn't still tough sometimes. It is. But the majority of it is gone. Recovery from depression is not a constant upward slope. But even if you have bad days, it does get better. Please be kind to yourself and don't hurt yourself. Stay safe. Thank you, Forest Interlude.

author: Roq M0Z
text:
Checkpoint: 

I graduated high school at 5'9 and 260 pounds. I was absolutely friendless with no direction in high school. I had no job, my depression was bad, and I was just going through the motions. The goal was to go to college because, well, that's what I was expected to do. I was terrified, I thought that I would never make a friend and that I'd have a degree in something that I wasn't cut out for. I had a stutter that was so unbelievably bad it sounded like I was beatboxing when I tried to say good morning.

I looked at the mirror and told myself "my stomach looks awful. My legs and knees hurt. When I stand straight up, my fat forms 3 rolls on either side... I mean I can get it down to 2 no problem, right? As silly as that sounds, that motivated me.

Fast forward 2 months later, and I'm ~230 pounds and eating much better. My college offered us an opportunity to do charity work or go camping or some other trip so we can make some friends before classes start. I'm in the bus headed to a Habitat for Humanity house that we need to build. I'm playing pokemon on my phone on an emulator when some dude arches his head over the bus seat and asks "are you really playing pokemon"

It was all too familiar, but instead of staying silent, my nerdy confidence took over.

"Hell yeah dude! My Venosaur is kickass, I'm on the 6th gym"

Silence.

I sat there wishing that I had never been able to talk, embarrassed out of my mind, knowing that I'd have to work with these people for a few days and my opportunity to make friends was over and I kept running over these thoughts over and over again in my head. From the front of the bus i heard fast footsteps "BRO WHAT GEN ARE YOU PLAYING"

I smiled as I showed him the fire red rom on my phone. He sat down next to me and I showed off my team and we were having a good time as more and more people came out the woodwork and started hopping into the conversation. That night, I had a few people that I was at least cool with, and when we got back to the dorms, I looked at myself in the mirror.

"I mean... I gotta look my best for my new friends. What's getting those 2 rolls down to 1?

Fast forward 3 months later, and I'm ~200 pounds and finally my back and legs don't hurt nearly as much on a daily basis. I can actually run now!
It's October, I was reading something and remember a character saying that it takes one good deed to make a person's entire day, so I attempted to do this. I saw a guy outside and attempted to make friends with him by patting his back and making a bad joke. In hindsight, that was stupid. He was drunk as all hell and turned to me and thought I wanted to fight. I tried to say a bunch of things, but I stumbled over my feet and my words and it came off as "Step off, dick". He was not happy. We were right outside my dorm building, so I scanned my way in and ran up to a random group of guys that I saw hanging out in a lounge. 

"Okay, I don't know you, but pretend we're friends. Some drunk dude wants to fight me and I really don't wanna deal with that right now".

A few sporadic laughs here and there ring out before I get the okay, and I sat there waiting. I looked over and saw them playing some weird game on their computers. Being a handheld and console kid I was confused as all hell. "Hey, what game are you guys playin?"


Fast forward a year and a few months later. I'm 170 pounds and lifting. I really hit it off with that group. I'm living with them all, taking up a chunk of a dorm. I'm finally starting to feel really good about myself. We do a bunch of stupid stuff as a group. I met a few friends of a friends that I noticed also had some self esteem problems. I wanted to give them the push that I never got, so I invited them to my dorm to hang out and play some video games. They were all great people, albeit shy and nervous. They needed confidence, so I called them together and boomed out:
"Fellas, we're going to the gym!"

Fast forward to present day. I'm still 170 pounds, and have been doing exercises at home to stay sane and in shape. The pandemic has me cooped up inside and I missed an entire year of hanging with those guys... or rather I would say that had I not had their discords and phone numbers and messaged all of them multiple times a week. Unlike people from before, the relationships aren't one sided. I will go out of my way to talk to them and they would do the same for me. A few of these people and I want to start a business after college and we are taking all the steps necessary to do so. In what? Well, most of us have been unified by one thing: video games. Had it have not been for my love of games and desire to take the first step, I never would have been happy in college and I would have stayed directionless. I most likely would've given up trying to lose weight after a few months, too. So, I hope to be able to make a game that could inspire at least one conversation and be the strength that at least one person needs to overcome their challenges. I want a game that me and my friends make to be that catalyst. Luckily, most of us are either Computer Science or Game Design majors.

I'm so happy. Some nights, I will sit down in bed and cry not because I'm sad, but because I truly can't believe that I'm this happy. Even something as awful as a pandemic couldn't break me. I made friends, am trying to build a company, gained my confidence back, and lost 100 pounds to boot.

To anyone reading this, if life has got you down and you feel like giving up, don't. Life is what you make of it. Bad times will suck, yeah, but I promise that the good times will be all the sweeter when they come. I believe in you!

author: Volgotha
text:
Checkpoint: 
.TW
.
.
.
.
In 2006 I started college, and from 2006 to 2009, life was pretty sweet. i made friends i had a boyfriend, I was doing alright in school and I got into my preffered art program. Then in 2010 everything started to downhill. First my friend group kind of dissolved. Then my boiyfriend dumped me, and then we had to put out cat down.
But the worst was what happened surrounding my mother. While going to college, I went to these clubspaces and made some friends there.

February 2011, my mother was dying of cancer. Someone from my old friend group, Tin, trolled me on steam the night I found out my mother had a year left to live. I was having a complete breakdown and exploded on them for picking the worst time possible to troll me. When I apologized to them, Tin demanded I admit to being a shitdisturber. Not wanting anymore bullshit, I ignored them and signed off of Steam. I posted to my wall, explaining the situation and asking for ppl to understand, but my cry for compassion was twisted as me using my mother's illness as an excuse to get away with being a bitch. That triggered someone well liked in the group, Kelly, who had previously lost her mother, which in turn pissed everyone else in the group off.
I remember the day she confronted me about it, I was warned by a then-friend, Shannon, that there was drama in the club so I went to investigate. I was confronted, verbally abused and left crying in the Oliver's caf with Shannon, while everyone else followed Kelly back to the club to confort her.

The situation was made ten times worse later that night by a certain person named Mathew, who took the opportunity to write a huge post on fb tearing me down, on which everyone else joined in taking a public jab at me. Matt was seen as the community leader at the time. He could have used his power to calm the situation down, instead he made things worse. To this day, I suspect that troll is the one who twisted my words to trigger Kelly and cause all of this, and that he also had Matt in the palm of his hand, but i digress; Matt's post convinced most of them to ditch me.

That devastated me in an already overwhelmed state, and I attempted suicide a few nights later.
That summer, I saw that my former friends were all having a big party, "What Killed the Dinosaurs? The Bad Movie Night.", and I wasn't invited. Shannon saw how much it hurt me, so she invited to her bf's party instead, and that's where I met Paul.
The following school year of 2011-2012 went by without much incident. The people who had ghosted me slowly added me back, Matt even apologized for his shit, and things seemed to be on the up and up. It looked like all this drama was behind us. I was wrong.
(these were friends I had made in the clubspaces I used to hang out at with my old friend group, samatha sarah ccameron and amber. Samantha and sarah had a falling out, and graduated so they stopped going to the clubs, amber left too, which only left cameron. Cameron is still my friend, but everyone else is gone. here ill explain sorry for the disjointedness of all this)
(oh and amber's still here. anyway)

After I graduated, I decided to go visit the club in Fall 2012.
I saw someone I knew, Sarah, crying on someone's lap, and asked her what was up. She told me she was in an abusive relationship with Tin. For giving her the advice to leave him, Tin came at me on steam again, and I told him that he was an abuser, that he would not intimidate me and to go fuck himself, and I blocked him. Suddenly, Matt was trying to extort 100$ from me for 2 locks I had broken the year before, which should've only cost 42$. Where did that come from? Well, Tin was the club's Treasurer that year. He was trying to get back at me for standing up to him and helping his victim escape, and he was doing it through Matt, who was going apeshit on me on MSN for refusing to pay 100$. I insisted I should only have to pay what I owe, which was 42$. He kept freaking out on me, so finally I threatened to get a lawyer involved, and that's when he backed down. I still paid the money I owed for the locks I had broken but I blocked Matt, having had enough of his bullshit, and that's when suddenly a bunch of ppl from the group ghosted me for good.
Why was I ghosted when Matt was clearly the one in the wrong? Because Tin. They ghosted me bc Tin told them to. Tin and Matt told them all sorts of shitty things about me and they believed them. They don't hold Tin or Matt to any of their shitty actions though bc they don't want the same abuse that happened to me to happen to them. They turn a blind eye to every shitty thing Tin and Matt do. It doesn't take a rocket scientist to understand there's an extremely toxic abuse dynamic at play in that group.
So, remember that party I went to with Shannon, and that guy I met named Paul? From 2011 to 2015 wer were together. I was isolated from whoever was left, only hung out with him and his friends. In 2014, I became close friends with a girl name d Ariel, a member of that old groiup who ghosted me. But that was probably a manufactured relationship manipulated into existance by Paul. because it turned out paul was a psychopath.

Paul was extremely abusive when no one was around. The night he left, we had a huge fight. I tried to escape the situation by running upstairs. He chased me and when I ran into my TV room and closed the door behind me, he started pounding on it and trying to push his way in. When he did manage to get through the door, I panicked, picked up a glass bottle and threw it at him, and then slammed the door again when he backed out. The bottle broke, and cut his finger very deep. He used that cut to get everyone present during the situation on his side. Nevermind all the crazy abusive stuff he had just pulled in front of them, no, I was the bad guy, and once he had them convinced, he left to my then bff's house, who later became his new gf.

He posted a picture of the wound on facebook, and because of that and previous drama from years ago that never really went away, most of the friends I had left from Dawson believed him, and ghosted me. I couldn't tell them that a week earlier he had raped me, and that's why I was scared enough to throw that glass bottle at him.

I filed a police report, I warned everyone who would listen to me about him, and I warned her. I've done everything I can, and I'm sorry for the friends I lost who believed such awful things about me.

I was too scared to tell them that Paul had raped me. I was too scared bc of previous drama that happened back in 2011, that drama bebing the stuff with matt tin and kelly.

I was too scared to tell this story for such a long time, because if asking for understanding while my mom was dying was twisted into me using my mom as an excuse to get away with being a bitch, then asking for understanding for the outbursts I had after being raped would just be twisted into me using my rape as an excuse to get away with being a bitch. I couldn't handle the idea of my rape being trivialized as just some excuse--and Mathew is in part responsible for it all, because of that fucking post he made publicly tearing me down. Had he not posted that, I would've never lost my support system, I would've never gone to that party with Shannon, and I would've never been raped.

So I spent the better parts of 2016-2018 telling those involved off for their part in my current situation and blocked them, and the rest rebuilding what I had back in 2009. Now I'm okay, I live with my fiance, who is very supportive and loving, we're making a game together which is something ive always wanted to do, and I have my old friends back. 

They're finally gone!

Now I'm making up for lost time doing everything I wanted to do but was ay too depressed; streaming, youtube, game dev, freelance illustration, writing a fanfic, etc. I feel free. I'm finally free from all of this. I feel amazing, and I can't believe I was able to go through all of this and come out the other side stronger and healthier than ever. I know what friendship feels like now, I know when someone's being an a-hole to me and I waste no time removing that from my life, I have healthy boundaries and I enforce them, and I'm surrounded by nothing but friends. 

I'm the strongest person I know. I used to think I was a weak pos,but nothing could be farther from the truth.

Hmm? Oh, welcome, traveler. I didn't expect anyone to stop by. Here, come warm your hands by the fire.

Have you eaten yet? Are you thirsty? Remember to take care of yourself. Not just your body, either; what nourishes your soul? What makes you happy? What keeps you going even when your flame runs out? A desire to succeed, perhaps? Or does love burn in your heart? Perhaps the eye wanders curiously?

author: Rachael B. Galicia
text: My best friend in the entire world is waiting for my words. So cheers love. I live with my father and we just moved into a house that I will inherit from him our forever home. Just got a new car in one my favorite shades of blue. I'm currently applying for a better job. I want to re-enter school once we settle in and flip our new pre-owned home and renovations are done our plans are to display our collection and also host our family gatherings since we became the go to. Life wasnt so easy to get here I still cry I still get flash backs I still have episodes and sometimes crippling anxiety. I still look back and it all feels like I dont deserve my current life style while still wanting more success and feel like I do I don't deserve more all at the same time. Ruminations run my mind and every day its a struggle to balance the positive and negative because I know I need both to function. Just driving to work or tidying a room or even to simply sleep can become easy or hard in an instant. And while life is supposed to be hard and I get that I still have yet to wait for the day when I can just take it easy just for a little while. I am grateful I don't for a second forget I am blessed. My conflict is internalized and unseen maybe I'll get my wishes maybe soon ill finally marry and have kids before I go gray. Maybe rest is tomorrow and I just don't know it but for the moment I just enjoy fixing up my house enjoying music visiting old friends working hard at a job I hate and enjoying my new car with very little sleep. All while trying to act like normal and push past the constant battles in my head. Maybe I dreamt it and it was all a night terror but that would be too convenient.

author: Radioactive Cheese: Now In Nuclear Reactor Flavour
text:
Life update time I guess?

I'm eating chips. Or fries in the magical world of America. Fat chips. I just ate dinner.
It's 9:23pm and I'm gonna study for a while. Sociology's going pretty good, all things considered.
Just watched an episode of Doctor Who. World Enough and Time. Brilliant episode. So's The Doctor Falls (might watch that tomorrow).
Also bought Assimilation2 Volume 1 (it's a Star Trek / Doctor Who comic) for only £20. Not bad, given that it's often rare and expensive as all hell.
I'll scavenge for Volume 2 someday. Hopefully soon.

You know, all this talk about Covid vaccines has made me feel a lot better about next year. Obviously the media's trying to boost public morale, and it'll still be a while before things really begin to go back to normal, but if we play our cards right, and don't get over our heads, we might just get our lives back. I've been thinking a lot about what uni may be like next year, if I'm actually able to go. It'll be nervous as heck at first, but I think it's gonna turn out incredible...

Live for the future, people. No matter how bleak it may get, remember that time never stops. Never. Things can change. Incredible things can happen from the worst of times.
Thanks for helping me realise that, Unus Annus.

This is Biggles, signing off for now.
23/11/20 (Happy 57th birthday Doctor Who!)

author: tami
text:
So this is my first internet checkpoint ig

I'm not developing a character here and I mainly wanna tell my backstory

A couple years back my grandmother died from possible improper care, I never got to say my goodbyes to her which is my biggest regret and because of that I feel like I can never move on from her death, I tried to stay strong throughout the years... but, I'm weakening over time, I have mental breakdowns more frequently now and my mother usually raises her voice at me if I don't tell her what's wrong. Which makes my mental breakdowns worse, I love my mother to bits and I can't really bring myself to tell her how that makes me feel as I don't want to hurt her feelings, but at the same time I do.

Now a few months back another one of my grandmothers died, just when I was getting better, which made my depression worse. My father is also hit hard by this loss as she was his mother, together me and my father are trying to fight through this step by step, but as he is getting better... I am getting worse, my mental breakdowns have become so frequent that it's becoming annoying to me and I'm hit by suicidal thoughts more and more.

I just wish things could be different, you know. I wish I wasn't a mess, I wish I could be happy again.

But I'm still up and fighting and I don't plan on giving up anytime soon.

author: Catcocomics
text:
It seems the flow of life is stifled in you, yet you continue to press on... an unfortunately common condition in this world and one that can so easily be overcome with the lessens of the Wind and Water.

Speak your truth, plain and kindly. Silence does not deter conflict from those with which you share a bond, letting those you love and trust in is crucial even in happier times, and even if all you can share with them is a simple "I don't know", you have at least presented them with a truth, something they may or may not be able to work with in order to bring you up a little better.

Life is a constant flow and ever moving, nothing can truly last forever. It is important to keep our loved ones in heart and in memory, so that when it is their time to depart, they will still be - in someway - by our side. One day you will rejoin them - it is inevitable that we all return to the Earth - but while our purpose persists, so must we.

author: Rene Montenegro
text:
In the last few weeks I got more and more suicidal thoughts. I feel like I have no special place on this world for myself. I'm an artist and that's what I wanna do for a living. I don't need luxury and a lot of money. I just want to make what I love. Art in any way... but here in my town and country it's hard to make money with that... and that fact is tearing me apart because I can't deal with people anymore... I got my closest friends around me and I'm fine with that. But I can't handle people any more... I can't... I don't want to... I don't understand people. Why are people treating each other the way they are doing actually... to see the world going worse and worse each day makes me leave this place earlier than I was supposed to... 
But now I stumble across those mysterious recommendations from YT which gives me nostalgic flashbacks to one if the best games ever made blessed with the best soundtrack list ever created, and reading so many comments from so many strangers around the world who are suffering with their own problems and most of them creating special checkpoints in their lives which are a big step for them, is making me feel so much less depressed. For a short moment I lose those depressions and thoughts because it shows me that my problems are truly not that much of a big deal. I should learn to appreciate what I have and can do. 

I wish you guys all the best I can imagine ! I hope those nostalgic flashbacks and feelings will be as special for you as it is for me.

This soundtrack kicks me back into my childhood where I used to play this game with my dad every time he came home from work. This memory is one of the greatest of all time.

Who ever you are, who uploaded those soundtracks years ago, thank you! Thank you so much !

author: Valcuda
text:
I've been commenting on random comments with the first things that pop into mind, and they seemed a bit weird to me.
Turns out, for some reason, my heart rate is lower than my normal average, and I'm quite dizzy, so I think the weirdness comes from low blood pressure.
But I shalt not let that hold me back! Low blood pressure me is the knight who just encourage his brothers and sisters and fellow friends to continue their journey of life! And give them advice to do so! Low blood pressure me is going to save hundreds of people, if not thousands of people from what ails them!
I just had a checkpoint in front of hundreds of brambles, so I shall be fine! If this is the end of the game for me, so be it! I have encountered my enemy Low Blood Pressure before, I know if I can beat him I will, and if I don't, then that shall be fate!
I will not let a simple bump in the steps make me fall down the stairs! It is my duty to ensure that my brothers and sister and fellow friends live the best best they can! And they shall know no best worst than the best best they can!
If my ramblings of unknown origin, of unknown fate, can have meaning to you, I have done my job! I have helped save someone from what ails them in this game of life, in the quest of unknown fortitude, of unknown origins, of unknown end, I have accomplished everything, have beat the game

author: Praise Me Heathens
text:
Ah, another checkpoint...  Not long ago I feared for the life of my mother. Now, I fear for it less but still, I must ask myself who I am. I don't know yet and I don't doubt that I am not alone. 

Together, staring into the nothingness before us all, we wonder what awaits us. Behind us are blue skies and lingering clouds and ahead of us, there are shadows and dead trees with a darkness that looms above them like a sinister omen for that which awaits us... yet still, we may see light within its center--hazy and obscured, yes, but a light nonetheless that lies beyond the foreboding veil. Not all of us in this world will make it through but that fear of loss gives value to what we have, so cherish these moments everyone. No game lasts forever and many of our companions will fall. The world is frightening, player, but there are times between our story arcs where we may rest, learn, and gather ourselves to journey into the terrific storm stronger and perhaps united by our differing ailments.

Steel yourself, player, as I do. Together we might yet discover who we wish to be, and when we meet know that when we do, I shall greet you with a smile.

author: Thomas
text:
Checkpoint September 8 2020

It’s been 6 months since quarantine started. The concept of time has been severely distorted for me. It feels like I’ve been re-living the same day for 6 months, and it’s especially weird since I’m at a bit of a transitioning period in my life. When quarantine started, I was a highschool senior. Our senior field trip, prom, senior prank, graduation, grad night, and saying goodbye to our teachers was all suddenly gone. Now I’m at my first semester in college, and I’ve never even been on campus. It feels like certain parts of my life have been on pause and other parts are continuing.
For college I’m majoring in Computer Science so right now I’m learning C. I’ve decided to expand on this and learn C#. I’m also looking to learn how to use the Unity engine, and I have a big idea for my first game.

author: kes the trashman
text:
Hello again friends, I hope you're doing well, you know I've been struggling with my anxiety and antisocial habits but i think i finally became someone im proud to be, myself. I've met my first actual love which between us its a bit weird and awkward considering we both haven't been in a relationship before but I do feel like there's something special between us that i never felt before. On the other hand my past has just been full of stress and high expectations. Everyone says i should go to college but i haven't even came close to thinking about that, ans the fact that i might not even be good enough for it. Somewhere in my childhood I somehow got to be "gifted" somehow but in hindsight it would have been better to just be with everyone else. Being the youngest by a decade from my brothers and being "gifted" put alot of attention on me and so either way my mother was too overprotective and never letting me go anywhere alone, always feeling like i need them or ill be lost and confused, and my mother never took me to meet new kids or outside anywhere really, so i didnt have friends growing up, and the ones i did have always left, always. At that point i never even felt a strong bond between me and someone else, so i wasnt even lonely, after all, you cant be lonely if you never experienced friendship before. But later in life i found a good friend of mine that i talked to and had fun with the rest of those 3ish years, actual friendship, now i would actually feel something if i was with no one around, which could be even worse, but that one friend eventually left but i made a friend quickly after, and we had plenty of time together, then i became more social, making people laugh, laughing with them, but soon after a fieldtrip together me and my friend separated, i felt alone in those months after, my friend left me, not even because they have to move or something, but because they disliked me, not even being able to look me in the face. Even other kids felt pity towards me. But by that time i was a completely different person, so i started to make friends with everyone, instead of sitting there alone, i talked to those people near me and i felt friendship toward them, proving that im not a sad lonely kid anymore that i can be like everyone else. At the same time i would make friends with my neighbours, who lived there just as long as me (my whole life) which tells you how much my mother was protective over me. Then i met my future crush and became the best friends.
Then of course the pandemic came which let me spend even more time with my crush and even develop feelings. So yeah basically my life story so far, at school i talk to people at lunch not anywhere else sadly cause everyone is quiet and shyer than me, and again the situation with my crush is happening so yeah my life has been crazy these past years . 
If theres one things to remember from this is to have faith in yourself and your decisions.

author: Thomas
text:
Update March 14 2021

Today's the one year anniversary since the lockdown started in my area. Things have changed so much in the last year; March 2020 felt like a lifetime ago. I don't know if it's COVID or post-highschool, but I began to drift from my friendships and didn't speak with many of them for a few months. I've since reconnected with some in the past week, but we still haven't seen each other at all in a year. I'm also struggling trying to make new friends in college. Most of my classes don't even have Zoom meetings, but in the few that do, everyone stays muted.
Back in September, when I was writing the original post, I was learning how to make a game in Unity. My original idea was really complicated for a beginner, so I scrapped it a few months in and started anew. The second game is now on itch.io, the first game I've ever released to the public. I'm still working on it regularly; I actually just implemented a few features yesterday.
So much has happened since September. I've moved for the first time in my life (albeit not far), contracted COVID-19 back in December along with the rest of my family (thankfully it wasn't serious), burned a few bridges, and rebuilt some other ones. Vaccinations are rolling out in my area, and I may be able to get it soon. I just hope this means we can go back to normal.



I wonder how long it'll be until I come back to this video again and write another update. Will we still be in a pandemic then?

author: misskippie
text:
I was so close to suicide. im on these anxiety meds and antidepressants that ive wanted to OD on due to a recent life event taking a huge toll on me. on the darkest days I would just lay in bed, not moving, not wanting to do anything because everything amplified my stress. i don't know what stopped me this summer from finally ending it, but I'm glad I didn't. maybe it just wasn't my time. im still alive and ive learned so many things due to this summer.

everyday im getting closure to my recovery from what happened to me this summer and prior events that im only now starting to confront and heal from. no longer am i the scared teenager I used to be, feeling worthless, feeling so alone in the world. i know I have people in my life who love me and are there for me. 

I forgive those who wronged me and hurt me. im learning from my mistakes I made that lead to my pain. ive grown up so much in these three months and for the first time im proud of myself and I love myself. im human I make mistakes and that's fine.

I value my friends, boyfriend and family who i took forgranted in the past. i know im not alone. i know not everybody is out to get me. im learning to trust and forgive again.

despite how scary and big this world is and how many bad people are out there, there are still people out there for you. if you feel alone, you just haven't met those people yet or you don't realize who's there. everything will be okay in the end. just keep going.

now that im recovering and that i survived this summer, I know im not weak or alone. im a new person this fall then I was last spring.

game saved.

author: Starukami
text:
Checkpoint:
9/4/2020
Man, this year has been an absolute disaster, hasn't it? I've moved so many houses, fought with so many people, lost friends, lost time. Almost failed my senior year because of depression and online school. Even now, in college, there have been days where I've felt lower than I ever have in my life, more alone than I ever thought possible.

But I'm not alone. I've got a girlfriend who loves me dearly, and friends that enjoy having me in their lives. Sometimes, we can lose sight of how much we truly have. School is rough for me, but I'm on track to get a degree and pursue my career. I got lucky with my scholarships, so I have no debt to worry about.

Life is good. Life is turbulent. But, a game's never perfect, nor is it always easy. That's what makes it worth playing. Keep grinding, everyone, and I'll see you at the next checkpoint.

Progress saved.

This is the second video like this I've been recommended, the first one being vines over a blue sky as most people probably know, so I guess it's time for another checkpoint :

Since my last checkpoint, life hasn't really been getting better, I feel like a failure and a disappointment for the few people I have around me, especially my parents. My anxiety is through the roof, can't finish university because of that because it's impacting my health but I have to find a job to live now so yeah. I'm stuck in a relationship with someone I'm not in love with because the way they're treating me is questionable and I miss one of my exes, the first one that I ever was in love with, you'll probably know the feeling like someone you'd truly do anything for, when you're with them, you feel more yourself than with everybody else even when you're on your own. They left me for someone else which wrecked me and that's not an understatement. I feel like giving up everyday when I wake up but can't because it would hurt my parents and the few friends I have but that's literally the only thread left I have. And finally, above all else, I feel guilty to feel like shit for such stupid bullshit like that when there are people having lives that are way worse than mine. So I wanted to apologise to everybody who is having way harder than me, I'm really sorry. I wanted to finish on a happy note but I don't know what I can say except they say it gets better with time so, if you want, if you ever feel like giving up watching this, know that somewhere there'll always be at least one person rooting for you and if I could I'd hug this comment section. Now it's time for me to get back on the road, I'll see you on the other side. Have a good one, I believe in you ❤

Checkpoint complete - 21/08/2020

author: AnywhereAndNowhere
text:
Checkpoint: Oh my god, I made it to Checkpoint 3 already. I'm starting to feel more excited when these pop up in my recommended feed now, and I don't entirely know why. I feel drawn to them now, no longer worried about coming across the wrong one at the wrong time. This might be a stretch, but maybe this is what people mean when they say that I'm meant to encounter them this way?

To recap from my last checkpoint, my partner had decided that they wanted to just be best friends with me, and I wasn't taking the change too well. I've had a history of bad breakups and abusive exes in the past that have tried to keep me emotionally invested in them in unhealthy ways even after they wanted to "remain friends", so it's hard for me to trust that this current partner-turned-platonic friend isn't going to turn out the same way. My self esteem has always been low, too, so this only reinforced my thoughts of being not good enough to have/keep a romantic partner. I used to have a group of friends that I could talk to before quarantine, but since then I haven't heard back from any of them, so maybe my problem is more that I don't have many people to talk to so I just get overly attached to the few people that do talk to me?

As of right now, I've been trying to put more time into the things I enjoy doing: making digital art, practicing animation, and I've recently picked up my old books that I loved writing so much during my middle school and early high school years. It helps to take my mind off things that still bother me, and I've been more productive now than I have been in weeks. Don't get me wrong, I'm still very lonely and my unhealthy thoughts still make it hard to rest easy in the evening, but I'm doing what I can to distract myself from those awful feelings and thoughts. This is the best I can do for myself, since I can't exactly ask for help at home. 

I should probably note that getting this all off my chest here is rather therapeutic. I don't know why, but it feels like a confessional- but without the religious undertones and the pressure of not wanting to be adhered to any one spiritual belief. Maybe at the next checkpoint I'll tell a bit more about myself as an individual?

author: Slightly Intriguing
text:
This video's title, きりのもり (kiri no mori), can mean both "forest of fog" and "forest of the end".

の (no) = possesive particle
もり (mori) = 森 = forest
きり (kiri) can mean two things. It can mean 霧 = fog, mist, but it can also mean 切り = end, finish.

Edit: I just found out that the correct 漢字 for きり is 霧, so it does mean "forest of fog". However, when said out loud it can mean either.

author: Manuel A. Hernandez-Estrada
text:
Huh, I just saw the last checkpoint yesterday. Not sure if I like the idea that I'm speedrunning life 😂 depends on what the goal is I suppose, haha.
Checkpoint:
I just woke up. Nothing different from my first checkpoint really. I guess I can talk about how I've spent a lot more time looking into the psychic abilities we may have, trying to reconcile these things with science and understand them without all the mysticism and myth surrounding many practical things we could do. I won't lie, weed helps to truly feel and recognize when this happens as you seem more connected and understood as you talk with people, or even watch videos over time and space. That's fun, wish it wasn't such a bastardized fun plant as we've made out to be lol. Oh well. Also still working hard on my music, excited to see where it goes. Catching ongoing wisdom as it comes. Playing up and down my fretboard hoping to reduce the bandwidth between its sounds and my brain to make them as a function. Also listening to more music to understand better how to compose, wondering if I should just be trying to win the lotto off feeling instead like intuitive greats like Kurt Cobain. We'll see. Other than that, trying to make friends with cool people on the internet, namely on twitter. But it's hard I guess, I think I enjoy people who are in their own little worlds, and I'd like to experience them. But to be in their own worlds they must be quite introverted, and you won't always find them wanting to share their world with others. It's a hit or miss game, either way it's cool I guess lol. Wow this one was a lot more positive than my first checkpoint at the other video. Hope you all have a wonderful day, and keep chasing your dreams. Any dream is worth dying for!
7/28/2020.

author: Tango Mango
text:
Checkpoint 1:
Date: 7/8/20
Time: 22:31
Stumbled onto these videos before, but I forgot to save my progress. Oops. But right now I'm a very gray area of my life. Not exactly depressed, but not exactly happy either. I don't have many friends, and my life is just very mondaine. I also can't get outside and explore the world much. (For obvious reasons, unless your somehow reading this in the far distant future, then congrats on finding this place.) I just feel lonely. Then I find my way here. I see all these comments about how they are going through rough times, and finding the strength in themselves to pull through. Coupled with the all the other positive messages, I just realized that I can do just the same. So to anyone reading this, whatever you're going through won't last forever, and you just need to summon the strength deep inside of you to make a better life for yourself. Wherever you may be, just know, WE ALL BELIEVE IN YOU. :)
SAVE COMPLETE

author: Brenda Kowalewycz
text:
Checkpoint.

I won’t say much, since I only recently saved a few weeks ago at the vines-in-the-sky checkpoint. Though I will say that things have been looking up since then, and the only reason I’m adding now is to remind myself that I am the main character in my story, and when I treat myself like that, all the little things, they matter, they add up. It’s almost like foreshadowing. 

So I want to remember that I want to foreshadow the good things, and not the bad. I’m putting in the hard work now, so that I’ll be able to level up fully by the time I reach my next checkpoint... whenever that is.

Let’s keep moving forward.
Saved. 11:43pm

author: Astiir
text: Sometimes I feel like the meaning to existence is so obvious that we can't accept it. It's something you can understand without language, or even a brain. Many times I found myself looking for a safety net like an afterlife to protect me from the idea of death. But now it feels like death is just an illusion, and the whole universe is just a timeless happening with no need to be explained or understood by me. It was us humans who gave the universe the obligation of needing to be understood, despite our inability to do so. In the quest for human knowledge, we usually end up with far more questions than answers. I think we should all be proud to play our part in the cycle of living. The only surety of life, is that unsurety will soon follow. But at least we aren't alone. For better or worse, we're stuck on this giant rock together.

Hey, man, highschool is fucking rough. You have no idea who the hell you are and so you have no idea how the hell to relate to other people, and it's so hard being young and anxious at the same time because of it. Over time you're gonna figure out what works by triangulating the differences between the people and events around you. You're gonna find out what feels right and that's the stuff that's gonna stick and fill you out.

The hard part is following through on the right shit, even if it's hard or terrifying. If you do, you're gonna be fine.

author: Brian Hernandez
text:
Hey, don't be so hard on yourself!
I spent a lot of my life feeling like I couldn't do anything right too- I mean even now I sometimes feel like that 😅
But there is no reason to beat yourself up about it! Just do your best! And take respite in the fact that you tried. We're all new to this life, and we're all figuring it out as we go along, so just... Try not to worry too much! Much easier said than done, I know.

And as for the rest, you will find your people soon enough. Maybe they're already around and you haven't realized it. But you will find them! Sometimes new party members show up in unexpected parts of the story, don't worry! And good luck!

author: The Glitch
text:
Checkpoint:  I fell asleep while watching the original blue sky vid and was gonna go back and write this there but I fee that ruins the magic. If its suggested again Ill leave a checkpoint but I'm here for now! Hello!. Anyways... 
I'm 15 years old and I'm starting to get into music writing. Im just finished writing one song and I'm ready to start my next one (if you got any cool words or phrases or ideas for the song just leave a comment). Someone close in my life is having detrimental health issues and I'm worried ill lose them for good. Also, me and my girlfriend are on a bad note right now. Originally I was going to end this with the idea that things are going to get better because of these videos. I could save here and leave. But I think in actuality, the checkpoint isn't here to magically fix your life... its to encourage you to help yourself. Its a resting point to regroup. Just calm down and let the world flow. It allows you to gather your thoughts and unwind for a bit. Then when you are ready to explore again, you will be ready for the future. I'm not gonna rely on a supposedly magic video series of game music to change my life. Im gonna work hard and change it myself. Anyways these are just my thoughts. I think ill save here for the night. 

SAVE GAME: Gamed saved at Wed, 24 Jun. 

Anyways safe travels everyone. this is me signing off.

author: João Samam
text:
Checkpoint:
Eu costumava jogar DKC nos anos 1990, com meu irmão, e minha mãe sempre ficava irada, pois nós só queríamos jogar ao invés de fazer qualquer outra coisa! Hoje fico pensando no tempo que eu podia ter ficado mais com a minha mãe, que faleceu em 2012, próximo da data do natal. Foi surreal, achei que ia morrer junto com ela de tanta dor que eu senti, e a pior das dores é a dor do abandono, de se sentir sozinho, como se ninguém pudesse para um pouquinho do tempo para lhe ouvir. Mas, minha família deu suporte, somos em 5 e cuidamos uns dos outros. Eu demorei um pouco para entender o amor do meu pai e o julgava sempre, brigava, porém, não façam isso, deem espaço para as pessoas lhes conhecerem. É importante termos pessoas iluminadas ao nosso lado,mas muitas vezes nos isolamos porque queremos, enfim, sejam livres, não julguem as pessoas e se permitam serem amados!

author: Adam Rummell
text:
Hello everyone, I'm not sure how I came to play this game called life to be honest. None of us are really, but I feel as if this isn't my first play through or my last. I feel as if we all are here for a reason. This video of course, one of the 4 so-called internet checkpoints; I'm not too sure why I'm here but I am so I might as well add.
I'm currently sitting in my room, in the middle of the Florida riots for George Floyd, coronavirus pandemic, and so far I've been pretty lucky in life but this year seems to have rolled a 1 on its CON save. Hopefully we all make it out alive for more years to come as a civilization. I'm a sophomore in highschool, I have a girlfriend, starting college classes next year for dual enrollment, getting a job and have anything I could ever want. But it's boring, I can't explain it but it is I don't know why either, I have all the friends I could want a great and loving family. But I feel out of place here in this world, it's not that I'm depressed, it's that I feel like there are so many others that could've came as a result from my parents meeting and I just got lucky winning. It's weird, I'm the only person in my house who doesn't like sports, you look at the rest of my cousins and siblings and they're all like 5'4" slim but then there's me, 6'2" broad shoulders towering over them, I'm the only one who is doing anything for college of the 5 of us (me and my brother and cousins) my oldest cousin is the one I'm most worried about tbh, he has no plans in life but if he wanted too he could do anything, my brothers only plan is the NHL, same with my youngest cousin, and the middle one she is just pampered by her had and ma being the only girl of the 5 of us. So I just feel kinda out of place for how I am but who knows we're all here for a reason maybe mine is to do something great but yeah that's enough of me I'm starting to sound narcissistic, how are y'all?

author: mmmyes
text:
I’ve talked about my loneliness on the video before this, so maybe another aspect of my life.




Maybe the sort of uncomfortable situation I’m in with a friend, but it’s one sided. There was a girl who very obviously liked me a few years ago, but self-confidence told me that she didn’t. She had been my friend for over 4 years at the time so I wanted to keep that.

Of course after that year she went to go get homeschooled and nothing happened until the next year when she came back. I didn’t even know she was coming back but when she did I realized maybe I did like her back. Self-confidence then pounded me again saying that she got over me and I believed it.

Fast forward about a month and then guess what? She and one of my best friends get into a relationship. I told no one about her so it wasn’t his fault.

It was painstakingly hard to not be uncomfortable when she was always with my friend when we were at school, but I feel like I got over it. 

In the end we’re just friends who had a weird past, but that’s probably the best outcome.

author: PapiJr408
text:
Im level 27 now in this game of life. 2020 the difficulty randomly just spiked to an insane amount with 0 warnings. 

In just this year alone I been experiencing worthlessness, insecurities, traumatic memories resurfacing, police brutality, racism, protests, global pandemic, my gf left me, my job cut my hours, im late to pay my rent, my co parent said she wouldn't help me renewal my apartment, I have to self isolate and be off of work for 2 more weeks which now it is a total of 8 weeks off, I was diagnosed with anxiety, im unsure if I want to do business, streaming or a corporate career, my car is still damaged from an accident I had, it overheats while im doing instacarts to earn money while I'm off work, I haven't played or streamed  anything in 4 days, im experiencing cognitive dissonance, im hungry but can't eat, i hardly sleep, I feel no motivation to do anything, I avoid people I love, im depressed & I feel like a burden.

With all of that going on im still pushing my hardest to experience all of life and enjoy what it has to offer the best I can. A stream friend [who I never met in person] and cousin of mine helped pay my rent off. Im so fucking grateful to Lone and Adrian. Real homies do exist out there. Be patient your people are out there looking for you.

 Oddly enough despite my negative feelings. Im hella excited to be single and work on myself. I was with my co parent since 17-25 and from 25-27 with my recent now ex gf. I need a relationship with myself now! I wont ever let anything or anyone in life stop me from achieving my goals no matter what. The hardest battle is finding the will to do it. Motivation on most days isn't enough. Some days I push extremely hard with 0 motivation.

Remember Friends exists. Love exists. Kill your ego. Love yourself. Treat everyone with respect. Know your worth. You're amazing. You're beautiful. Keep moving forward. Accept your mistakes. Keep learning and growing. Follow your goals, dreams, and desires. Feed your mind positive self talk. If you read this please save using any heart and i hope your journey is filled with many many more wonderful life experiences fellow main characters. 🤍🖤🤎💜💙💚💛💛🧡❤💖

Edit: 
Posted on: Thursday June 4th 2020

author: Inkke
text:
Checkpoint 2 - June 1st, 2020:

This year has been crazy from the start. We began with high tensions between the US and Iran and then the Australian fires became really big news. 
Then soon after word of the “mysterious” virus in Wuhan became big. It was identified as a Coronavirus and was spreading rapidly throughout China. Most people in the US thought it wouldn’t be a big deal, including the president. The first confirmed case in the US was in Seattle, WA. From there cases slowly rose as officials tried to keep the virus under control. 
In March, I got out of school for spring break, and I never returned. Schools were being shut down as well as non-essential businesses. The virus from that point on infected a lot of people. I liked watching the “Yakko’s World but coronavirus cases” on YouTube. Eventually the US became the number 1 country with COVID-19 cases. Life has been pretty stagnant until recently. 
A man named George Floyd was murdered by a cop, and it set the cap off for so many protests around the US and even other countries. Riots have broke out, but there are still many peaceful protests. My state has declared a State of Disaster in response to the riots. I hope the outcome of this will be a good one and a real change happens. 

To look back on in the future and remember 2020 and what has happened

Much Love~

I am extremely self conscious and care to much about what people think of me, my ego is extremely important to me. Because of this I get very scared whenever someone I care about sees a bad part of me. For example recently my sister was helping me with algebra. Think of that, I got angry to the person for trying to help me! Even then I got very angry and told her to shut up any time she told me anything.

Due to the current situation above I also get scared when I can't do things I normally can. I feel like a shell of what I'm supposed to be. An absolute failure of a human- one that can only dissapoint and do nothing good.

I guess it's because I'm in my teenage years and still have plenty of time before I make any big decisions but I fear that. I fear that I'll make the wrong decisions and dissapoint everyone around me.

I hope that I will solve my problems, and inner demon. Thankyou for reading all the way through my horribly written biography.

author: Neg
text:
Checkpoint 4
3:40 AM, CA, USA

Things are wild in the news today. I'm scared, to be honest. I feel so helpless with all the things happening in the US right now. I'm really feeling the weight of just being one person, and everywhere I look on social media, there's just nothing but terrifying news. I want to help do something, but I feel like my voice will be drowned out anyway, because why would the people with power here listen? They've already proven that they don't. On the other hand, I want to disconnect because of how much this is weighing down on me, but is that ignorance? Am I just running away? Everything feels like it's crumbling right now, and I'm scared. I can't sleep and I have a headache...

I think I'll stay a while. Everyone please be careful out there. Give my regards to the next MC you meet.

author: Delsin Jones
text:
My Name is DelsinJones, i’m a Youtube Creator 
I still live with my parents, i’m 21 years old, and this thing we call Life.. isn’t easy.
I honestly have a hard time being motivated to continue trying to be what i want to be. My Family has a negative outlook on almost everything and as good as a job i do by ignoring that, it affects me in ways i can’t describe. It hurts when they say mean things to me, pointing all their faults towards me that i haven’t done. I want to Give up, but if i want to make it in this Life, that ain’t an option. I know if i were to move out i’d be able to be more motivated to be a better Creator, but moving scares me. I’m afraid.
I’m afraid i’ll be Homeless
I’m afraid my Family will say: “i told you so”
I’m afraid that i’ll have to give up my Dreams..
Being Creative is Difficult, making videos is difficult. 
Just recently my Mother decided to call me out on me having a bad attitude on life, yet anytime i try talk to her about my life or anything personal it ends with her being mad, even my dad it’s always been this way. Even as a Child. I ask for someone to listen, to help me vent, i have no one. As a child my Mother said to me: “this is your Home. No one can take it away from you” and just the other day she said: “just remember you live here for free, and i can take that away from you” even a Mother can and will hurt their Son. I feel like my Trust for my Family is slowly Fading..
I want to have someone to talk with, someone like a friend, a friend who would listen, a friend who would care. Maybe some day...

The music is coming to an end, it’s 2 in the AM, and i’m tired. Maybe Tomorrow will be a better day. 
Thank you reading, if you read this, that means i, as a creator, showed you apart of who i am, and reached out to you for help. 

Goodbye..
Friend.

15-03-20

author: Kevin Dances
text:
I'm turning 30. I'm getting ready to move 4 states away from where I've lived all my life. I'm unsure about everything, especially rn with all this quarantine stuff. Being essential it hardly affects me, but it impacts everyone I know. I'm the only one doing business as usual.

Even though it can sometimes be difficult to get to the next point in your life, you will get there. Believe in yourself. Just make an effort to begin, and don't start anything you don't plan on finishing. Things will get better.

Stay strong, internet.
From your friendly long haul truck driver. 

PS: David Wise wrote the soundtrack for DKC and DKC2. Thank him for the incredible music he composed on this 16-bit console. No VG soundtrack comes close.

I missed. 
M16, stupid, thing to finally tell literally anyone... you know the front sight post at the end of the rifle? Well I had the trigger facing away so I could reach down and squeeze. Putting my head against what I thought was the barrel, I fired and put a holy in the roof of my CHU (little, container houses we lived in) and gave myself tinnitus. So yeah, I'm still here for a reason. It's kind of dumb sometimes, but I'm glad I'm not as smart as I thought I was, if I could fail that hard at killing myself I would be given the epiphany that I'm not even qualified to even be confident it's the way. Once you shoot 5.56mm point blank past your head, the universe wants you to look up ... author: Quinn Daniels
text:
@Ayda  I've sat here for a while trying to think of an answer, and to be completely honest, I don't really know. I mean, I don't know if there's just one specific reason.

I've tried writing a couple of reasons, but none of them felt like satisfying answers, and I'm not sure how much hope or wisdom I can convey, but I'll do my best. Hell, at one point, I started going into a smallish story-of-my-life type of response, but for that I'd need to write a novel, though I'd blame most of the length to my ADHD. But, I digress.

The initial night before the day that I had planned to kill myself the year before, May 19th, I had a bad emotional breakdown. It was more draining than any others I've had before then. It was to the point that it drained any energy I'd had and I ended up spending the entire day in bed. I felt horrible about it, and instead I put it off until May 22nd, the Friday of that week. I thought that would be enough to get some of my affairs in order.

On a whim, I invited a couple of my friends to my house for that Thursday to try out a game that they'd wanted me to try out for a couple of years. Again, I don't really know why. I guess I just wanted to see them one last time. I hadn't planned on telling them anything.

One of my friends, the first friend that I actually made when I started school in kindergarten, arrived first, and we had a good time together until some of my family arrived with little to no notice beforehand. Suddenly I have my attention split five different ways, one to my brother and sister-in-law, one each for my niece and nephew, one to my friend who was also socially overwhelmed, and one way failing to calm my raising anxiety.

Somehow I use an excuse that allows both of us to go outside, u bothered, when our other friend pulls into the driveway. He sees that we're overwhelmed, so he takes us on a little drive to eat and sit in his car to listen to music.

While we're listening to music, we talk a bit. Again, I don't know why, but at some point, I just whispered, almost to myself that I had bought a rope. I couldn't even bring myself to look up as it dawned on my friends what I was alluding to.

My oldest friend climbed to the back seat and hugged me and comforted me while I had a breakdown that I had kept bottled up for years. Something about my friends just being there hit me so hard. I had believed and convinced myself that I must be sub-human — where I believed that I deserved all the bad things that happened to me in life, whereas anything good that happened to me were undeserved or fraudulent. Not only that, but I am an extremely touch-starved person, and being held and told that I did deserve love and compassion helped me to start chipping away at the toxic barriers I put around myself when I was younger.

I don't know if my answer is enough to do your questions justice, but if you have anymore, I'll be happy to answer it.

And it's never to late to try to become the best version of you that you can be.

author: Quinn Daniels
text:
I came dangerously close to killing myself in May. I had all the preparations ready, just like I had planned for a year before then. The day before I planned to go through with it, I impulsively invited a couple of my friends over to see them one last time. The day didn't go as planned, with family stopping in unannounced, and me becoming overwhelmed to the point where we had to leave the house to calm down.

I still don't know why I quietly mentioned that I had the rope. I guess I still had a speck of hope somewhere within me that fought to see my future, to not want to constantly feel inhuman.

Now, in a couple of weeks I'm going to a college that I never imagined that I'd make it to, to pursue a career that I had given up hope on, and soon I'll be able to get therapy and hopefully be able to transition and hopefully become the person I never thought I would reach.

I guess what I'm trying to say is, if you can keep living, then I want to keep living too. Maybe things aren't as worthless as I once thought

Hello Friends,
If you are anything like me, then when you found this you thought the comments may be a meme that you may have been missing out on. It is not.
Relax. Stay for a bit. We do not judge here. Let the music envelope you. Feel the moment.


We are all sharing this exact same moment at different times and in different lives. Maybe you found this weeks, months, or years from now. Or maybe weeks, months, or years in the past.
Whatever brought you here, just know everyone is glad you made it. We will meet again and you will again understand.

author: OPALpersonal
text:
This is it. You've seen it all. Pewdiepie has left for his expedition of real life. Markiplier currently embarks on his journey with Ethan. You know they'll all be fine. 

Onision is dead and buried, James Charles remains on a shaky throne over cracked support... You've experienced a lifetime of Youtube drama, but you've also experienced the best of times. ASDF Movie, The good Youtube Rewinds, Jacksfilm's YGS 100, it's all under your belt. You've been a true pioneer, a veritable adventurer throughout the Youtube scape. 

From Vaporwave, to Game Grumps compilations. From entire readings of the Bee Movie script, to GMod mashup memes.

And this is your reward.

You stand at the end. The edge of the system. For beyond here, there is nothing. Nothing but that endless sky, forever out of reach through the vines and entangled thorns. A peaceful, yet melancholy tune accompanies the wall between the realm of content, and the realm of the unknown that stands just inches away. You float here, on the inside, looking out into what else could be.

You contemplate. Would it be worth it to break out? To struggle through the trees and make it into the vast, foggy emptiness, forever to run into a void of dim clouds and gentle music? Or are you content to turn back into the familiar territory, and return to the Guitar Hero Memes and Vinesauce monthlies, the Relaxing Video Game Music mixtapes and perfect game speedruns?

Perhaps, just maybe, it's alright to stay here for a moment. Or for a little while.

To listen to the music, and look outside at what could be , just beyond your realm.

At the edge of the internet.




~You found: Edge 3/4~

author: J M
text: Not a single bit of music was something I could listen to without thinking about my ex. We weren't together for too long, but he broke my heart and strung me along for such a long time after we separated. I've always used music to break away from feeling trapped by my feelings. Somehow, simple things like this. From games. Makes me feel safe again. And I haven't managed to do that without the help of a person in years. Thank you. And to everyone reading, this is your message that the pain will go away soon. Stay safe. Be strong. You will be okay. The sun will rise again.

This song remembers me when I was very desperate to find a girl and even to feel how does it feel to be near of a girl in a romantic way. I did many stupid things and I was even one step close to ruin my life. It started on January, 2019. Then for some surprises of life I had the chance to meet the most beautiful (sexy) girl of my Uni. In a day which I lost all hope she come around me and hug me in a very seductive way; since I was sad and since I am a man with "needs" I accepted her game. Few months ago and with a crazy story in the meantime we started a formal relationship. We have been together 1 year and 3 days hehe. This is a totally weird relationship she is 3 years older than me and the only thig she do is fucking working all the time in her farm while I am a very relaxed man of 24 years that only play videogames and works when I can/have to. She is not into videogames neither music... Sometimes I do not know how we reach hapiness being a couple but I can say that I love that woman.

author: Valcuda
text:
Here's a tip my fellow traveler, sometimes when everything is just bottled up, and you feel like you shall explode with emotion, sometimes it just best to let it all out in a public space of some sorts where you can remain anonymous.
Just knowing it's out there, out there for others to see and know, but know who, just let's you relax and find inner peace, even if it comes along slowly, repairing the shattered bottle known as yourself.
And when it finally does, take a long hard look at yourself and ask, how can I make myself better, better in the such that you enjoy yourself better.
We are are individuals, what we are is who we are, and we are ourselves, and we exist for ourselves, so don't let anyone change you, or tell you to not be who you are.

author: External
text:
Everybody feel lost at one point in their life. It's not okay to think there's only yourself. Remember we're on a huge ball of rock and water floating around a giant ball of energy without a purpose in a universe nobody had catch a glimpse of at least 0.00001% of it. It's normal to feel lost. Don't let this feeling invade your mind. Even if the universe is huge you can progress through it like in a dark forest. As long as you are giving yourself a direction to follow you will make it. If you want to experience something you will have to progress and never stop till you reach the goal. Your gf might have cheated on you, your family might think you're a disappointment, your boss might think you're an expendable being for the bank account of a rich guy watching everyone from above in his mansion in the hills, but keep in mind that this is a copping mechanism to not fell to lost in the universe. You are worth more than their vision of yourself, believe me. Even the most confident guy that is banging the best looking girls in the world is lost. You are not alone. 


If you want to end it all, drop your rope, put the pills away, unload your gun. This is not the end...
I love you. I believe you can be the best you. Stay safe. Enjoy life.

author: Spicy Tuna
text:
My father was an abusive drug addict, but when he wasn't using, he had a tendency to be not half bad. We were extremely poor growing up. This game is one of my earliest memories from the late 90s (the SNES was pretty cheap by then). When we got it was well before the time he turned out abusive to my brother and me. Before we'd ever been beaten for anything. It reminds me of the innocence I had. When I could view the whole world through those rose tinted glasses. And for a few minutes, I get to have that little bit of myself back. Even if only for a few minutes.

I'm getting better.

Thank you.

author: ThunderDragonRandy
text:
That one video was "Stickerbush Symphony" while this one is "Forest Interlude", both from Donkey Kong Country 2, composed by David Wise.

Their Japanese song titles from Super Donkey Kong 2 (the Japanese title of the game) are "Toge Toge Taru Meiru" (とげとげタルめいろ "Thorn Thorn Barrel Maze") and "Kiri no Mori" (きりのもり "Misty Forest") respectively.

"Stickerbush Symphony/Toge Toge Taru Meiru" is played during the bramble-themed levels of DKC2/SDK2 while this song "Forest Interlude/Kiri no Mori" is played during the forest-themed levels of DKC2/SDK2.

author: Grucketts
text:
I can sense the feeling and emotion in the image
>its been a long car ride
>your going camping with your parents
>you packed bug spray, lotion picknick supplies and a tent
>but most importantly of all you planed to make smores
>you finally find a nice camping spot
>dad sets up the tent with mom while you go searching for firewood
>its bit humid but you have only a shortlsleeve shirt on so you get a little chilly
>you find a nice log
>its heavy
>you really want to impress your parents so you attempt to bring it back
>you start heading back as dirt gets caught in sandals
>you feel somethings really wrong
>relization kicks in that your lost
>you look up at the towering trees as leafs fall
>your allergies begin to react
> you wander in a different direction for a bit
>you find a pond as bugs wirr around you and your runny nose
>its getting a bit late
>sky begins to turn dark as you gaze past the shaking trees
>your shivering
>scared
>confused
>you drop the log
>you kinda just stand there ask the darkness consumes you
>all you here are crickets , water flowing and occasionally bush rustling
>rustling gets louder
>its heading towards you 
>somehow your legs start moving on there own 
>your running away from whatever you heard 
>somehow yo managed to wade into the water and trip on a slippery rock
>you get a cut and the water stings it
>youve given up now
>crieing
>You here a woman shouting "hang on don't run in there fella"
>you relise it's a park ranger
>she says something through the radio but your to traumatized to understand 
>she picks you up and quickly brings you somewhere guided by a dim headlamp
>by this point you tired and falling asleep
>sleep

>you wake up inside the camping van
>you try to stand up but you leg cuts itself again
>you wander outside in search of your parents
>you find youre dad by a campfire 
>you smell something slightly burnt but toasty
>smores!.png
>you rush outside 
> trips on ledge of door step
>dad runs over
>son are you ok?! He frantically says
>yea I'm fine
Then he eats you 
Dead

author: Chuck Hadokens
text:
I'm 30 years old and my mom passed away this past february 2019 and today October 1st is her birthday, the first birthday without her here, I remembered how she loved this song along with the bramble scramble stage when she would watch me play Donkey Kong Country (she bought all 3 for me and donkey kong 64) on the super nintendo when I was a kid. Since there was no youtube back then I would just go to the stages and put the controller down so we could enjoy the music. In my sadness today I'm glad I was able to come across this track by accident. :,)

Edit: Thank you for the outpouring of kind words and support. I'm a private person and I normally would never share my feelings like this on facebook and much less youtube. It was just an alternative way to get it out as my grief counselor and hospice programs suggest and I didn't want to concern friends and family flooding my post with sad and heart reacts even with it being the best of intentions.  Anyway this is getting too long but thank you everyone again.

text: https://discord.gg/D6d5nBK Hey Chuck and everyone reading this, this was a beautiful comment and I really admire your ability to pour out your soul here where people can resonate with you... We have a dedicated server for anyone who's stumbled upon these videos, where we can all share vibe and spread good energy together. It's a safe space where everyone is permitted, with dedicated mental health channels if you all would like to vent or just get your thoughts out so everyone can be there for each other. We started on February 5th and we already have over 150 members, if anyone here wants to join, I would love to know you all a bit better <3 this is my favorite comment section on YouTube, I want to preserve this love and keep moving it forward in a devoted community, I hope you all hear me out and consider joining!! author: James Payette
text: Hey, I am about a month late, November 1st 2020, happy belated birthday to your late mother.  I hope this comment finds you well. even though over a year has gone by since you posted this, others still come and see your story. They see many more as well! and despite never playing donkey kong country, I understand. we each have out own story. my mother has stage 4 kidney disease right now and is fighting to get at home dialysis, and she loves final fantasy. 13 in particular despite what others might say about it. and to who may stumble upon this or any other comment here. stay strong. the year is 2020, its harsh. I know everyone shares the sentiment, but I hope next year is better. let's fight for a brighter future, for us, and for everyone else.

author: Chuck Hadokens
text: @TomberryTCG  Hello bro, reading your story brought me to tears! My sincerest thoughts go out to you my brother. Your mom sounds like she was a wonderful beautiful soul. Thank you for replying and sharing your memories with me as well. I'm happy to say I'm coping better than I was a year ago but  like you so eloquently put there's not a day that goes by that I don't miss her. I pray, hope, and wish nothing but the best for you, your family, and your loved ones for the rest of this journey called life <3

author: TomberryTCG
text: Chuck... this comment hits home harder than anything else ive read. I lost my mom to cancer after she fought for several years. The last six months of her life were the hardest days in my 31 years alive. I have never cried and laughed so much ever with her. She too loved watching me play my SNES for hours on end, asking if there was anything she could do to help me clear any level i was having issues with (even though she was horrible at video games). After my father left her when I was 11, she and i became best friends as i grew up. We would talk in the late night hours about relationships i was in and out of. This coming March will be 3 years since her passing and not a day goes by that i dont miss her and hope that I make her proud of the choices ive made in my life! Thank you again for sharing this and I hope as everyday passes, it gets easier and a little brighter for us!

author: Chuck Hadokens
text: @Angelizar  Thank you for your well thought out and beautiful words. And thank you for listening to it to honor her. I'm really at a loss for words but a million thanks really. And even though the pain will always be there I'm in a better place mentally this year than I was last year. Thank you again brother and best wishes to you in life and all your endeavors.

author: Angelizar
text:
Thank you for sharing this beautiful story Chuck. I found your comment today so I figured it would be nice to let you know that I'll honor her by listening to this song. I know losing someone is something devastating but remember, when you listen to music they used to like or do things they used to enjoy, they are right there with you. The fact that they are not there physically doesn't mean you can't connect with them cherishing the times you spent together. 
Happy birthday to your mother, my best wishes to you.

author: turidayobaka w
text:
幼稚園の頃、親父がこのゲームとスーファミ本体を買ってきて一緒にやった。
俺はディディー、親父はディクシー。
毎日親父が仕事から帰ってくると二人でいつもやってた。
それを後ろで見守ってくれる母親と妹。
結局、ラスボスが倒せず俺は放棄してしまった。
そんな俺を横目に親父はなんとか一人でディディーとディクシーを駆使してラスボスを倒し、俺に自慢してきて今度一緒にまたやろうと言ってきた。
けど、俺はその時には熱が冷めていてどーでもよかった。

現在、親父も母親ももういない。
あの時家族一緒にゲームが出来てた事がどんなに幸せだった事か。
あの頃に戻ってクリアできなかったラスボスに一緒に挑戦したい。
最近、一人でやって全クリしたけど、虚しいだけ。

ごめん、親父。こんなバカで親不孝者で。
ホントにごめん。
